President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an order to reduce direct spending budgetary resources for fiscal year 2024 in non-exempt budget accounts. This reduction will take effect on October 1, 2023. The amount of the reduction will be calculated by the Office of Management and Budget and specified in their report to Congress on March 13, 2023. The sequestrations will be carried out in accordance with the requirements of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act and the specifications outlined in the Office of Management and Budget's report. The order was issued on March 13, 2023, from the White House.